Read and parse log file as a data frame.

read_log.Rd

Read and parse log file as a data frame.

read_log(file)

Arguments

file

A path to the CSV file or a CSV formated string. First row starts with values without headers.

Value

A data frame object with three columns sorted by these columns:

  • timestamp: (dttm) Ordered timestamps of ping.

  • address: (chr) IPv4 address of server.

  • ping: (dbl) Elapsed time in msec, or NA in case of timeout.

Examples

# Prepare data
log_csv <- paste(
  "20200101000001, 192.168.1.1/24, 5",
  "20200101000002, 192.168.1.1/24, 8",
  sep = "\n"
)
path <- tempfile()
writeLines(log_csv, path)

# Read from path and string.
read_log(path)

#> # A tibble: 2 × 3
#>   timestamp           address         ping
#>   <dttm>              <chr>          <dbl>
#> 1 2020-01-01 00:00:01 192.168.1.1/24     5
#> 2 2020-01-01 00:00:02 192.168.1.1/24     8
read_log(I(log_csv))

#> # A tibble: 2 × 3
#>   timestamp           address         ping
#>   <dttm>              <chr>          <dbl>
#> 1 2020-01-01 00:00:01 192.168.1.1/24     5
#> 2 2020-01-01 00:00:02 192.168.1.1/24     8
